That was nineteen-seventeen. By the next year I had a few beaux\
myself, and I began to play in tournaments, so I didn\'92t see Daisy very\
often. She went with a slightly older crowd\'97when she went with anyone\
at all. Wild rumours were circulating about her\'97how her mother had\
found her packing her bag one winter night to go to New York and say\
