I suppose he\'92d had the name ready for a long time, even then. His\
parents were shiftless and unsuccessful farm people\'97his imagination\
had never really accepted them as his parents at all. The truth was\
that Jay Gatsby of West Egg, Long Island, sprang from his Platonic\
