rooted shyly into her mother\'92s dress.\
\
\'93The bles-sed pre-cious! Did mother get powder on your old yellowy\
hair? Stand up now, and say\'97How-de-do.\'94\
\
Gatsby and I in turn leaned down and took the small reluctant hand.\
Afterward he kept looking at the child with surprise. I don\'92t think he\
had ever really believed in its existence before.\
\
\'93I got dressed before luncheon,\'94 said the child, turning eagerly to\
Daisy.\
\
\'93That\'92s because your mother wanted to show you off.\'94 Her face bent\
into the single wrinkle of the small white neck. \'93You dream, you. You\
