\
\'93Yes,\'94 admitted the child calmly. \'93Aunt Jordan\'92s got on a white dress\
too.\'94\
\
\'93How do you like mother\'92s friends?\'94 Daisy turned her around so that\
she faced Gatsby. \'93Do you think they\'92re pretty?\'94\
\
\'93Where\'92s Daddy?\'94\
\
\'93She doesn\'92t look like her father,\'94 explained Daisy. \'93She looks like\
me. She\'92s got my hair and shape of the face.\'94\
\
Daisy sat back upon the couch. The nurse took a step forward and held\
out her hand.\
\
\'93Come, Pammy.\'94\
\
\'93Goodbye, sweetheart!\'94\
\
With a reluctant backward glance the well-disciplined child held to\
her nurse\'92s hand and was pulled out the door, just as Tom came back,\
