\
\'93Are we just going to go?\'94 she objected. \'93Like this? Aren\'92t we going\
to let anyone smoke a cigarette first?\'94\
\
\'93Everybody smoked all through lunch.\'94\
\
\'93Oh, let\'92s have fun,\'94 she begged him. \'93It\'92s too hot to fuss.\'94\
\
He didn\'92t answer.\
\
\'93Have it your own way,\'94 she said. \'93Come on, Jordan.\'94\
\
They went upstairs to get ready while we three men stood there\
shuffling the hot pebbles with our feet. A silver curve of the moon\
