bootlegger the first time I saw him, and I wasn\'92t far wrong.\'94\
\
\'93What about it?\'94 said Gatsby politely. \'93I guess your friend Walter\
Chase wasn\'92t too proud to come in on it.\'94\
\
\'93And you left him in the lurch, didn\'92t you? You let him go to jail for\
a month over in New Jersey. God! You ought to hear Walter on the\
